commit_message:
Sync log from oslo

Update the copy of oslo's log to oslo-incubator
0533894d6bfacd82a371bccd628b61d5016032cd.

This is the first step towards supporting Python 3 in
os-collect-config.

Change-Id: If282091d7f0cbd4e2ce90d70c066bb11cbf56d38

commit_message:
Apic drivers enhancements (second approach): L3 refactor

- refactor to leverage Client's transactional capabilities
- General refactor to improve the driver's reliability

Implements blueprint: apic-driver-enhancements

commit_message:
l2pop: Allow network types overridable

Currently "tunnel_types" is used for two different purposes; l2pop and
check_segment_for_agent.  This commit introduces a new agent
configuration "l2pop_network_types" to allow overriding the former.

This will be used by ofagent, which wants l2pop info for TYPE_VLAN
as well.

Related: blueprint ofagent-l2pop
Related: blueprint ofagent-merge-bridges
Change-Id: Ia83a94b6661aa36afa8bfeb073101171ffde62a9

This is looking good, and, with one simple fix mentioned in-line, works with the hierarchical binding unit test in https://review.openstack.org/#/c/116209/. 

I've also added a comment about needing to be able to also match on segmentation_id when looking for an existing dynamic segment.

One remaining concern is that there is currently no way to have separate pools of network segments of the same type for allocation as tenant networks and for allocation as dynamic networks. I'm not sure if this is likely in practice, but if tenant_network_types includes 'vlan', and VLAN dynamic segments are being used for hierarchical bindings, tenant networks could get allocated from the physical networks and ranges intended for use as dynamic segments. 

Perhaps network_vlan_ranges could be made to indicate, for each range, whether its to be used for tenant network static segment allocation, or for dynamic segment allocation. This might be done by preceding ranges for dynamic segments with a special character. Alternatively, a separate config variable could be used to define the ranges for dynamic segments. Regardless of how its configured, I think distinguishing these would require adding a boolean to the VlanAllocation model class, and filtering on this in the query to find a free VLAN."}, {'account_id': 107, 'date': '2014-08-22 17:44:53.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 9:

One more thing occurred to me regarding cleanup of dynamic segments. The delete_network() method in plugin.py has the following code to return the static segments of a network to their allocation pools before the segment records themselves get deleted via cascade with the network:

                        for segment in mech_context.network_segments:
                            self.type_manager.release_segment(session, segment)

We need to make sure both static and dynamic segments are released. I'd suggest replacing the code above with a call to a new TypeManager.release_network_segments(self, network_id) function. This would do a database query for all (static and dynamic) segments with the specified network_id, and then call release_segment() on each returned segment's driver. commit_message:
Fix a minor defect in the manual for Trusted Compute Pools

The command used as a sample in the manual to set a flavor is not correct in Juno.

Closes-Bug: 1362899
Change-Id: I89b4aa6d3de67d300769cda1d7c9847a5a34ad2b
Signed-off-by: Dave Chen <wei.d.chen@intel.com>

commit_message:
xenapi: make boot from volume use volumeops

Currently the boot from volume code path has partially duplicated code
with the connect_volume method in volumeops and get_vdi_uuid_for_volume
in vm_utils.

This change removes the code duplication by calling volumeops to connect
the volume when doing boot from volume. For dependency reasons, this
means moving get_vdis_for_instance from vm_utils into vmops.

The unit test test_vdis_for_instance_bdi_password_scrubbed only checked
that auth_password was scrubbed if it was passed into the logging in a
certain way. The test now checks that auth_password is actually
passed into the logging in that way too.

Change-Id: I8591f30b177db38073a0145b902b607bb012a18a

commit_message:
XenAPI support: Changes for networking metrics

Implemented inspect_vnic_rates() to inspect the vNIC rate statistics
for an instance.

Change-Id: Ic8fb59904f5ff8fc05819b9414b7730b8746bfad
Implements: blueprint xenapi-support

commit_message:
Add Bigswitch plugin in migration that creates 'agents' table

For creating table 'networkdhcpagentbindings' table 'agents' is
needed to exist, but Bigswitch plugin was not added to the
migration_for_plugins list in migration 511471cc46b_agent_ext_model_supp.
Also added to 1fcfc149aca4_agents_unique_by_type_and_host that modifies
'agent' table.

Closes-Bug: #1337216

Change-Id: I7e16ccb79088247e678dc1ca799aff9481edbd61

commit_message:
Unify option tables a bit

This unifies some placement of entries into tables accross projects:

glance, trove, neutron, keystone, cinder: Changed ssl to ca.
Move debug to debug if such a table exists (ceilometer).
Move default_log_levels to logging.
Create logging section everywhere and unify content.
Move fatal_deprecations to logging.
Move host to common.
Move lock_path to common.

Change-Id: I461f90a7d6b05aa5c113244c978c933039dde08c
Partial-Bug: #1363485

commit_message:
ofagent: Enable local arp responder for local VMs

Because ofagent makes every arp requests packet-in and
perform packet-out anyway, just make it respond arp requests
for local VMs.  It would be simpler and more effective than
forwarding requests to the network as it did before this change.

Before this change:
    request: src VM -> switch -> controller -> switch -> target VM
    reply: target VM -> switch -> src VM

After this change:
    request: src VM -> switch -> controller
    reply: controller -> switch -> src VM

As a bonus, now we can test l2pop and local arp responder with
a single node setup, at least for some extents.

Related: blueprint ofagent-l2pop
Related: blueprint ofagent-merge-bridges
Change-Id: I606a238d8c2021ed908fbd89d3488768497f57c5

commit_message:
VMware: fix test_snapshot_delete_vm_snapshot_exception* tests

Mocking away time.sleep() for the purpose of counting number of calls
to it has unintended consequences after integration with oslo.vmware
This modifies the test to track the calls through a function wrapper
class that additionally calls time.sleep() with zero wait to speed up
the tests.

version 2: provide wrapper to time.sleep and mock call to wrapper
instead.
version 3: also remove another skip.

Change-Id: Ie99c5cf095d09f093e7b2f617e007dbace174299
Closes-bug: #1363349

commit_message:
ofagent: merge br-tun into br-int

Highlights:
- Deprecate br-tun.
- Reduce the use of OFPP_NORMAL action.  Use mac address info
  obtained from get_device_details and l2-pop to reduce flooding.
- Use OpenFlow metadata instead of "internal" VLANs.
  Now tenant networks are VLAN transparent.

Implements: blueprint ofagent-port-monitor
Implements: blueprint ofagent-merge-bridges
Change-Id: I21ee1c6d141863182b487e10c7bfe911b1a472ab

commit_message:
Use 'replica' instead of 'slave'

The term 'slave' is very mysql specific. Deprecate the API terminology
that references 'slaves', and 'slave_of', and replace it with 'replicas',
and 'replica_of' instead which is more applicable across datastores of
different types.

Co-Authored-By: Greg Lucas <glucas@tesora.com>
Change-Id: Ief4bc83369fa3183a321d3e07b69b1801595ab15
Closes-bug: 1360310

commit_message:
Add a drop config-grp command in update instance

As per the current code in the client, there is no option to detach
the configuration group of the instance. This change gives a user the
option to explicitly drop the config group of the instance as part of
the instance update call.

Change-Id: I7defd110549df87afd267d3ebe998904ff6b7483
Closes-Bug: 1359359

commit_message:
controller for the endpoint policy extension

The controller level of the extension is really just a
marshalling function, with the exception that it is responsible
for catching any delete notification events for the entities
that are part of endpoint policy associations.

Implements: bp endpoint-policy
Change-Id: I4c5e9e9cff392f917a9d79a798ff72df2f48e6d1

commit_message:
Refactor client models in python-barbicanclient

Switching to an OOP approach.
Also did some minor cleanup (removing old Verifications code and some
unused imports).

Change-Id: Ifb443eb0a3ca7bab570d9181b35f6fd5f09e727c
Implements: blueprint client-refactor-models

commit_message:
Implement validation on the Catalog V3 API

Use JSONSchema to validate CRUD operations on V3 Catalog resources. This
includes wrapping the create and update methods for Regions, Services,
and Endpoints. This change removes functionality specific to the Catalog
API for validating parameters for incoming requests.

Closes-Bug: #1284430
bp: api-validation
Change-Id: If8b665ffb0ed22a3f060254786fe1feaf0b78318

commit_message:
Change v3 flavor_access to v2.1

This patch changes v3 flavor_access API to v2.1 and makes v2
unit tests share between v2 and v2.1.

The differences between v2 and v3 are described on the wiki page
https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/NovaAPIv2tov3.

Partially implements blueprint v2-on-v3-api

Change-Id: I75891e76753fba937b4a01f592afb4bd03aacd9c

subject: Convert v3 flavor extraspecs plugin to v2.1

commit_message:
Convert v3 flavor extraspecs plugin to v2.1

This patch changes v3 flavor extraspecs plugin to v2.1 and makes v2
unit tests share between v2 and v2.1.

The differences between v2 and v3 are described on the wiki page
https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/NovaAPIv2tov3.

Partially implements blueprint v2-on-v3-api

Change-Id: Ibf42ad56ead33846d57904dde2a07f721e6e4af3

commit_message:
Received notifications context is not a DesignateContext

Nova/Neutron's notifcations context contains fields which we do not
know how to handle in DesignateContext. We should treat received
context's as simple dict's rather than attempting to munge into
a DesignateContext.

Change-Id: Ieda187679171333be69e98d6301c64a14187a5d7
Closes-Bug: 1360696

Specify namedtuple_as_object=False when using simplejson

commit_message:
Sphinx 1.2.3 doesn't work for us

Sphinx released version 1.2.3 on September 1, 2014. Things are
now breaking. Joshua Harlow has filed an issue:
https://bitbucket.org/birkenfeld/sphinx/issue/1553/sphinx-apidocpy-line-56-python3
This patch pins sphinx to avoid the new 1.2.3 version.

Change-Id: Ie0c096cceb8b2e48d40091d6195bb52e4aabff9e

commit_message:
Improve api_paste_config file searching

Currently, if the file defined by api_paste_config is not found under
working directory, it will use etc/ceilometer/api_paste.ini instead,
this is because at that time, devstack doesn't support the new config
file. After patch I57165d588da35f13b2d22629b48dc087502598a7 is merged,
this workaround is no longer needed, and we should use advanced
find_file() provided by oslo.config to search config file.

Meanwhile, if the file is found under working directory, we should use
absolute/relative path instead of bare base name, otherwise, the
deploy.loadapp will not work.

Change-Id: I9bcb7b69a0159d548401de1c36f773a1965722b6
Closes-Bug: #1329126

revisions:
[{'created': '2014-06-17 06:05:32.000000000', 'message': 'Allow reset-state on attach and migration fields

This modification adds support for reseting attach status and migration
status of volume.

usage of the commands:
usage: cinder reset-state [--state <state>] [--attach-status
<attach_status>] [--migration-status <migration_status>] <volume>
[<volume> ...]

Explicitly updates the volume state.

Positional arguments:
  <volume>         Name or ID of volume to modify.

Optional arguments:
  --state <state>  The state to assign to the volume. Valid values are
  "available," "error," "creating," "deleting," and "error_deleting."
  OPTIONAL: Default is available.
  --attach-status <attach_status>  The attach status to assign to the
  volume. Valid values are "attached", "detached". (Optional,
  Default=None)
  --migration-status <migration_status>  The migration status to assign to
  the volume. Valid values are "migrating", "starting", "completing",
  "error", and "none". (Optional, Default=None)

This modification is based on the patch:
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/88083/

DocImpact

Change-Id: Icdce16510434b188a7f62ecef2c84a514f4560b1
Closes-Bug: #1308253

commit_message:
Allow reset-state on attach and migration fields

This modification adds support for reseting attach status and migration
status of volume.

usage of the commands:
usage: cinder reset-state [--state <state>] [--attach-status
<attach_status>] [--migration-status <migration_status>] <volume>
[<volume> ...]

Explicitly updates the volume state.

Positional arguments:
  <volume>         Name or ID of volume to modify.

Optional arguments:
  --state <state>  The state to assign to the volume. Valid values are
  "available," "error," "creating," "deleting," and "error_deleting."
  Default=available.
  --attach-status <attach_status>  The attach status to assign to the
  volume. Valid values are "attached", "detached". Default=None.
  --migration-status <migration_status>  The migration status to assign to
  the volume. Valid values are "migrating", "starting", "completing",
  "error", and "none". Default=None.

This modification is based on the patch:
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/88083/

DocImpact

Change-Id: Icdce16510434b188a7f62ecef2c84a514f4560b1
Closes-Bug: #1308253

revisions:
[{'created': '2014-08-04 09:29:56.000000000', 'message': '  New heat templates for Openshift-Origin deployment using scalability functionality

  Author: Antoine Abélard
  Date:   Mon Aug 04 11:30:00 2014 +0100

    New heat templates for Openshift-Origin deployment using scalability functionality.
    Templates are based on the Openshift-Origin template (https://github.com/openstack/heat-templates/tree/master/openshift-origin/F19). The aim is to add scalability functionality to this template. Metric use for the scalability are cpu_util and nbgears. This second metric is a custom metric implemented by a bash script calling by cron to get from the broker node the number of gears used and the number of node connected, to determine when a new node is needed. The data is send to the Ceilometer V2 API and used in the heat template.
    I implemented 9 templates :
    aws format :
      - openshift (1 node and 1 broker)
    hot format :
      - openshift (using last version of puppet modules) :
        * openshift (1 node and 1 broker)
        * openshift-scalable-cpu (scalable openshift environment using cpu_util metric)
        * openshift-scalable-nbgears (scalable openshift environment using nbgears custom metric)
        * openshift-scalable-cpu-nbgears (scalable openshift environment using cpu_util metric and nbgears custom metric)
      - openshift-production (using fixed version of puppet modules wich has been tested) :
        * openshift (1 node and 1 broker)
        * openshift-scalable-cpu (scalable openshift environment using cpu_util metric)
        * openshift-scalable-nbgears (scalable openshift environment using nbgears custom metric)
        * openshift-scalable-cpu-nbgears (scalable openshift environment using cpu_util metric and nbgears custom metric)

Change-Id: Idfdf158ff6176c5ef6902e27a6e764e23171cf4c
Implements: blueprint heat-openshift-templates

commit_message:
New heat templates for Openshift-Origin deployment using scalability functionality

    New heat templates for Openshift-Origin deployment using scalability functionality.
    Templates are based on the Openshift-Origin template
    (https://github.com/openstack/heat-templates/tree/master/openshift-origin/F19).
    The aim is to add scalability functionality to this template. Metric use
    for the scalability are cpu_util and nbgears. This second metric is
    a custom metric implemented by a bash script calling by cron to get
    from the broker node the number of gears used and the number of node
    connected, to determine when a new node is needed. The data is send to
    the Ceilometer V2 API and used in the heat template.
    To avoid compatibility issues due to changes in this project or
    in Puppet modules it depends, versions parameters are provided in hot templates.

    I implemented 5 templates :
    aws format :
      - openshift (1 node and 1 broker)
    hot format :
      - openshift (1 node and 1 broker)
      - openshift-scalable-cpu (scalable openshift environment using cpu_util metric)
      - openshift-scalable-nbgears (scalable openshift environment using nbgears custom metric)
      - openshift-scalable-cpu-nbgears (scalable openshift environment using cpu_util metric and nbgears custom metric)

Change-Id: Idfdf158ff6176c5ef6902e27a6e764e23171cf4c
Implements: blueprint heat-openshift-templates

commit_message:
Add "parent" key to list stacks output

Pass back the stack owner_id (parent stack ID) via the RPC API, then
expose it via the "parent" key when listing stacks.  This will be
None for all top-level (non nested) stacks, so can be ignored when
show_nested is not passed.

blueprint: list-nested
Change-Id: I5ad7f867bc7eb138bf2d7d17b4a3bf810d341393

commit_message:
Use oslo.i18n

Module `gettextutils` from common code was graduated to oslo.i18n, so it
would be great if we reuse this library.

Change-Id: Ie5836b82723fc80c1d54e5e65eac8565cf905c5a

commit_message:
collector: Allows to requeue a sample

This change allows to choice the behavior when the dispatcher method
fail.

Now we can requeue on the messaging bus the sample by setting:

[collector]
requeue_sample_on_dispatcher_error=True

This only works when the sample have been publisher with the notifier://

DocImpact
Change-Id: I4a2ad60613aa7ac2c7e90996821be0a4fc018ccf

commit_message:
Add length constraint to Nova Keypair's name property

Sets min/max bounds of the Nova Keypair Resource's name
property to 1 and 255 respectively.

Change-Id: I48fb25eee465938fd7e48e105187d1646c8c64c0

commit_message:
Make version.py handle pbr not being installed

Since pbr is now only a dev/build-time requirement of taskflow
and not a run-time or test-time requirement we should not have
a version file that explicitly requires pbr to exist to function
correctly.

To accommodate when pbr is not found use the pkg_resources function
that can provide the installed version instead so that we still
provide back a valid version.

Change-Id: Id191d2b38def54b95a3467b4023a9540c284660d

commit_message:
Add a None option to the CONSOLE_TYPE setting

We where able to set the CONSOLE_TYPE in local_settings.py, but not able to
deactivate it.

We added a new option to CONSOLE_TYPE which is None.
To keep the legacy behaviour, CONSOLE_TYPE defaults to 'AUTO' and has to be
explicitly set to None to deactivate the console.

implements bp hide-vnc-console-access

Change-Id: Id23f3d5e37509b846858d480ad781f2b4ffc3590

commit_message:
Stack breakpoint specification

This specification describes a feature to help troubleshooting
a failed stack.  Stack breakpoint allows the user to pause a stack
create or update at a point before the failure so the user can debug.
This will leverage the new lifecycle callback mechanism.

Change-Id: Ib83e558dd522a663c350df81fca833658596af5d

Add show_nested parameter to GET v1/stacks API

Adds an optional argument which can be used to enable listing of
all stacks, including nested stacks

Hi Li, thanks for the patch!

Propagating the exception error message to the user in the UI has been discussed before, and the consensus is that it is not a good idea. You can find a more detailed discussion in this mailing list thread (see especially Gabriel's reply): http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack/2014-January/004649.html

What you can do in this case is:

1) If a more specific exception is thrown in the case of quota error, catch it and display a more specific error message. (Something very similar is done in this patch: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/68137/3/openstack_dashboard/dashboards/project/images_and_snapshots/images/forms.py).

or

2) Using the nova API, check quotas beforehand, and refuse to do the modification if it would result in an inconsistency."}, {'account_id': 9, 'date': '2014-02-09 06:03:13.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Abandoned

Hi Li. Thanks a lot for addressing my concern. It looks much better now. I just have two suggestions:

1. Sorry to be nit-picky, but I was wondering if we could improve a little bit on the wording of the error message. Current error message is "Quota value needs to larger than already used, instances used: #, cores used: #, ...". What do you and others think about this: "Quota value cannot be less than the current usage value: instances used: #, cores used: #, ...." (ends with a fullstop)?

I agree with Cindy that erroring on the actual field would provide a better user experience. But I'm ok with your current approach too as it's consistent with most other modal forms.

2. I am now thinking this change would deserve its own test case, where some project quotas are set to less than the usage numbers and have it error out.'}, {'account_id': 4428, 'date': '2014-02-19 01:33:22.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 8.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-02-19 01:33:23.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 8:

commit_message:
Quota error message should be more descriptive

forms.ValidationError will be raised if there are invalid quota values.
The error message would be like: Quota value cannot be less than the
current usage value: ram used: 512, instances used: 1.

Change-Id: I6734de7df6c146d647bbc89090d49a48e1b074ae

commit_message:
Move DNS packet serialization into mDNS service

This ensures that all middleware + the final application (handler) has
full access to the request and response message objects.

The current tests will need to be re-worked in a future commit.

Change-Id: I1ee3ec0cd5384af31592e075cb08b137ba9a353e

commit_message:
Improve usability of base.Scenario.validate()

By default Validator() shouldn't raise any exception, cause it is
not catch by validate method. To make validate more safe we should
catch any exception from validators and convert them to
InvalidScenarioArgument exception.

Change-Id: Ib685617ccef1cc62e0e7a49bb5392e6fe44f6a55

commit_message:
Impove benchmark validation and cleanup benchmarks decorators

*) Use @validator for all validation
*) Use new approach in all benchmarks
*) Change order of decorators in benchmarks
*) Unify required_parameters
*) Imporve validation tests

Co-authored-by: Boris Pavlovic <boris@pavlovic.me>

Change-Id: I74eb00af6f2b6a574fa0368c3dc36dd4011014d7

commit_message:
Implements queue, message and claim controllers for Redis

This patch implements the standard controllers for the redis
storage driver. It has been tested against a localhost Redis
server with ZAQAR_TEST_REDIS=1.

Change-Id: Ib7c100afd11a0410c3f241c1925d5aaf172ce6a8
Partially-Implements: blueprint redis-storage-driver

[{'created': '2014-08-08 00:29:37.000000000', 'message': 'Do not rely on hash ordering in tests

With tox 1.7.2 hash randomization will be on by default, causing
random failures of tests. How to reproduce:

commit_message:
Do not rely on hash ordering in tests

With tox 1.7.2 hash randomization will be on by default, causing
random failures of tests. How to reproduce:
* Update tox
* Run something like:
  $ for i in {1..20}; do tox -epy27 || break; done

Changes to fix:
* Made most of generated stuff predictable by adding sorting
* Added serialized dict check for schema validation

Change-Id: I36934ce1ebfa0c98ed9fcba6e42617c0d1b2e195
Closes-bug: #1348818

commit_message:
Add API schema for v2.1/v3 user_data extension

By defining the API schema, it is possible to separate the validation code
from the API method. The API method can be more simple.
In addition, a response of API validation error can be consistent for
the whole Nova API.

Partially implements blueprint v3-api-schema

Change-Id: If58e67a7fa0d256e307e565bb983c12ea131e439

commit_message:
Add observer role to benchmark tool

This patch introduces a new observer role, which lists messages but
does not claim them. As part of this work the config options were
updated and the defaults adjusted to provide a better "kick the
tires" experience.

The default number of procs and workers is now hard-coded rather
than being based on number of available CPUs, since the number of
workers you may want to run is more dependent on the size of your
Zaqar deployment and your network bandwidth than it is on the
number of CPUs on the load generator.

Finally, the "-pc" suffix was removed from the command name. This
was included in this patch because it didn't seem significant
enough to split out.

Change-Id: I8a8190fb2cebc3489c78da4f6e1e7c51d8b97017

commit_message:
labs: pass vm_name as arg to _vbox_configure_ifs

_vbox_configure_ifs should no longer use the environment variable
NODE_NAME as the name of the node VM. It gets replaced by the correct

commit_message:
Change v3 hosts to v2.1

This patch changes v3 hosts API to v2.1 and makes v2
unit tests share between v2 and v2.1.

The differences between v2 and v3 are described on the wiki page
https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/NovaAPIv2tov3.

Partially implements blueprint v2-on-v3-api

Change-Id: I8ce66570edb06bde0bdea677e6e784539aaab763

commit_message:
Sync time on slaves after hard reset

We perform hard reset of slaves in system
tests for Ceph, but it is very time sensitive,
so time synchronization after nodes boot should
be added.

Change-Id: I226b4ca20164c1635e86265f7483de8e28c950e5

[{'created': '2014-09-01 10:17:53.000000000', 'message': 'Added vcenter support for ostf tests.

Because in the configuration with vCenter compute node is missing, added:
1. Getting type of virtualization from cluster settings
2. Processing case when the type of virtualization is vmvare (not checked for no compute node available)
3. In test_sanity_infrastructure compute node has been replaced by a controller because
   for vmvare and neutron interaction occurs via controller node

Implements: blueprint vcenter-hv-full-scale-support
Change-Id: I4f74011de5548990f163f220632fbf4fe2ffa39e
'}]
commit_message:
Added vcenter support for ostf tests.

Because in the configuration with vCenter compute node is missing, added:
1. Getting type of virtualization from cluster settings
2. Processing case when the type of virtualization is vmvare (not checked for no compute node available)
3. In test_sanity_infrastructure compute node has been replaced by a controller because
   for vmvare and neutron interaction occurs via controller node

Implements: blueprint vcenter-hv-full-scale-support
Change-Id: I4f74011de5548990f163f220632fbf4fe2ffa39e

revisions:
[{'created': '2014-08-27 13:12:02.000000000', 'message': 'Add parsing of hypervisor deployment tags

Patch include:
* Deployment tag qemu|kvm
  added in  the sanity.test_sanity_infastructure for
  tests: Check internet connectivity from a compute,
  Check DNS resolution on compute node. This give for us
  possibility not discover those tests in case if vcenter
  is set as hypervisor
* Add parsing of hypervisor
  date into fuel_plugin.ostf_adapter.mixin.py
* Add check for  libvrt_data
Change-Id: Idce25c31c0f001aa1a71fb790b912cddea6fb85b
Related: blueprint vcenter-hv-full-scale-support

* Add parsing of hypervisor

* Add check for  libvrt_data

commit_message:
Add parsing of hypervisor deployment tags

Patch include:
* Deployment tag qemu|kvm
  added in  the sanity.test_sanity_infastructure for
  tests: Check internet connectivity from a compute,
  Check DNS resolution on compute node. This give for us
  possibility not discover those tests in case if vcenter
  is set as hypervisor
* Add parsing of hypervisor
  date into fuel_plugin.ostf_adapter.mixin.py
* Add check for  libvrt_data

Related: blueprint vcenter-hv-full-scale-support
Change-Id: Idce25c31c0f001aa1a71fb790b912cddea6fb85b

commit_message:
Introduce DEVSTACK_GATE_UNSTACK env variable

When this variable is set to "1" environment created by devstack will be
removed by calling ./unstack.sh.  This is beneficial for installing
dependencies while not being interested in running openstack services.

Change-Id: I47cd842edc44858e6f487a425de0ab7a68ba4cf8
Related-Bug: #1360658

revisions:
[{'created': '2014-02-07 11:37:00.000000000', 'message': "Port to oslo.messaging

The oslo.messaging library takes the existing RPC code from oslo and
wraps it in a sane API with well defined semantics around which we can
make a commitment to retain compatibility in future.

The patch is large, but the changes can be summarized as:

    * oslo.messaging>=1.3.0a4 is required; a proper 1.3.0 release will be
    pushed before the icehouse release candidates.

    * The new rpc module has init() and cleanup() methods which manage the
    global oslo.messaging transport state. The TRANSPORT and NOTIFIER
    globals are conceptually similar to the current RPCIMPL global,
    except we're free to create and use alternate Transport objects
    in e.g. the cells code.

    * The rpc.get_{client,server,notifier}() methods are just helpers
    which wrap the global messaging state, specifiy serializers and
    specify the use of the eventlet executor.

    * In oslo.messaging, a request context is expected to be a dict so
    we add a RequestContextSerializer which can serialize to and from
    dicts using RequestContext.{to,from}_dict()

    * The allowed_rpc_exception_modules configuration option is replaced
    by an allowed_remote_exmods get_transport() parameter. This is not
    something that users ever need to configure, but it is something
    each project using oslo.messaging needs to be able to customize.

    * Finalizing the port from RpcProxy to RPCClient is straightforward.
    We put the default topic, version and namespace into a Target and
    contstruct the client using that.

    * We maintain a global NOTIFIER object and create specializations of
    it with specific publisher IDs in order to avoid notification driver
    loading overhead.

    * rpc.py contains transport aliases for backwards compatibility
    purposes. setup.cfg also contains notification driver aliases for
    backwards compat.

    * The messaging options are moved about in cinder.conf.sample because
    the options are advertised via a oslo.config.opts entry point and
    picked up by the generator.

    * We use messaging.ConfFixture in tests to override oslo.messaging
    config options, rather than making assumptions about the options
    registered by the library.

Change-Id: Ib912809428d92e788558439e2d85b51272ebefdd

    pushed before the icehouse release candidates.

    * The new rpc module has init() and cleanup() methods which manage the
    global oslo.messaging transport state. The TRANSPORT and NOTIFIER
    globals are conceptually similar to the current RPCIMPL global,
    except we're free to create and use alternate Transport objects
    in e.g. the cells code.

    * The rpc.get_{client,server,notifier}() methods are just helpers
    which wrap the global messaging state, specifiy serializers and
    specify the use of the eventlet executor.

    * In oslo.messaging, a request context is expected to be a dict so
    we add a RequestContextSerializer which can serialize to and from
    dicts using RequestContext.{to,from}_dict()

    * The allowed_rpc_exception_modules configuration option is replaced
    by an allowed_remote_exmods get_transport() parameter. This is not
    something that users ever need to configure, but it is something
    each project using oslo.messaging needs to be able to customize.

    * Finalizing the port from RpcProxy to RPCClient is straightforward.
    We put the default topic, version and namespace into a Target and
    construct the client using that.

    * We maintain a global NOTIFIER object and create specializations of
    it with specific publisher IDs in order to avoid notification driver
    loading overhead.

    * rpc.py contains transport aliases for backwards compatibility
    purposes. setup.cfg also contains notification driver aliases for
    backwards compat.

    * The messaging options are moved about in cinder.conf.sample because
    the options are advertised via a oslo.config.opts entry point and
    picked up by the generator.

    * We use messaging.ConfFixture in tests to override oslo.messaging
    config options, rather than making assumptions about the options
    registered by the library.

The oslo.messaging library takes the existing RPC code from oslo and
wraps it in a sane API with well defined semantics around which we can

The patch is large, but the changes can be summarized as:

    * oslo.messaging>=1.3.0a4 is required; a proper 1.3.0 release will be
    pushed before the icehouse release candidates.

    * The new rpc module has init() and cleanup() methods which manage the
    global oslo.messaging transport state. The TRANSPORT and NOTIFIER
    globals are conceptually similar to the current RPCIMPL global,
    except we're free to create and use alternate Transport objects
    in e.g. the cells code.

    * The rpc.get_{client,server,notifier}() methods are just helpers
    which wrap the global messaging state, specifiy serializers and
    specify the use of the eventlet executor.

    * In oslo.messaging, a request context is expected to be a dict so
    we add a RequestContextSerializer which can serialize to and from
    dicts using RequestContext.{to,from}_dict()

    * The allowed_rpc_exception_modules configuration option is replaced
    by an allowed_remote_exmods get_transport() parameter. This is not
    something that users ever need to configure, but it is something
    each project using oslo.messaging needs to be able to customize.

    * We maintain a global NOTIFIER object and create specializations of
    it with specific publisher IDs in order to avoid notification driver
    loading overhead.

    * rpc.py contains transport aliases for backwards compatibility
    purposes. setup.cfg also contains notification driver aliases for
    backwards compat.

    * The messaging options are moved about in cinder.conf.sample because
    the options are advertised via a oslo.config.opts entry point and
    picked up by the generator.

    * We use messaging.ConfFixture in tests to override oslo.messaging
    config options, rather than making assumptions about the options
    registered by the library.

Implements blueprint: oslo-messaging

commit_message:
Port to oslo.messaging

The oslo.messaging library takes the existing RPC code from oslo and
wraps it in a sane API with well defined semantics around which we can
make a commitment to retain compatibility in future.

The patch is large, but the changes can be summarized as:

    * oslo.messaging>=1.3.0a4 is required; a proper 1.3.0 release will be
    pushed before the icehouse release candidates.

    * The new rpc module has init() and cleanup() methods which manage the
    global oslo.messaging transport state. The TRANSPORT and NOTIFIER
    globals are conceptually similar to the current RPCIMPL global,
    except we're free to create and use alternate Transport objects
    in e.g. the cells code.

    * The rpc.get_{client,server,notifier}() methods are just helpers
    which wrap the global messaging state, specifiy serializers and
    specify the use of the eventlet executor.

    * In oslo.messaging, a request context is expected to be a dict so
    we add a RequestContextSerializer which can serialize to and from
    dicts using RequestContext.{to,from}_dict()

    * The allowed_rpc_exception_modules configuration option is replaced
    by an allowed_remote_exmods get_transport() parameter. This is not
    something that users ever need to configure, but it is something
    each project using oslo.messaging needs to be able to customize.

    * We maintain a global NOTIFIER object and create specializations of
    it with specific publisher IDs in order to avoid notification driver
    loading overhead.

    * rpc.py contains transport aliases for backwards compatibility
    purposes. setup.cfg also contains notification driver aliases for
    backwards compat.

    * The messaging options are moved about in cinder.conf.sample because
    the options are advertised via a oslo.config.opts entry point and
    picked up by the generator.

    * We use messaging.ConfFixture in tests to override oslo.messaging
    config options, rather than making assumptions about the options
    registered by the library.

Implements blueprint: oslo-messaging

Change-Id: Ib912809428d92e788558439e2d85b51272ebefdd

commit_message:
Add idmap to libvirt config

Allows Nova to configure libvirt domains with id map
elements. This allows user namespaces to be enabled
and configured.

Partially implements: bp libvirt-lxc-user-namespaces

commit_message:
Fix nova boot failure using admin role for another tenant

When user create instances with admin role for another tenant
and specify a security group which name is duplicated in Neutron.
Then user will run into an error and from the GUI, and user can't
know what happened.

The root cause is the method find_resourceid_by_name_or_id doesn't
honoured the project info. So this fix will specify the project id
for find_resourceid_by_name_or_id(), so this patch depends on the
neutron client fix, see: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/103476/,
which has been merged.

Change-Id: I478ff4faa013a822483e39c8f5153a3a1e777f9b
Closes-Bug: 1335733

Remove old policies from policy.json

They're confused, misleading, and most importantly unused.

commit_message:
Networks are not scheduled to DHCP agents for Cisco N1KV plugin

With the config option 'network_auto_schedule = False' in
neutron.conf, networks do not get scheduled to available DHCP
agents. The fix is to explicitly schedule the network as part
of the subnet creation flow.

Change-Id: Id1f94a5844111a916f984d6dd7bda2cb4e11e1ee
Closes-Bug: #1356609

commit_message:
Remove node parameter from power_off() method in virt driver

The Nova virt driver power_off() method does not have a node
parameter, and the parameter is not used in Ironic - so
remove it to make it consistent with the Nova driver.

Change-Id: I3c23155d8c4ae6bfdb094e07a86b832121349816

commit_message:
Reimplement Volume snapshot with backup

Use backups instead of snapshots for volume handle_snapshot: it allows a
better management of a lifecycle of the stack snapshot, because cinder
snapshots can only exist along with the original volume.

blueprint stack-snapshot
Co-Authored-By: ala.rezmerita@cloudwatt.com

Change-Id: I1ec2bd177df61cae05769628c63db0bd0790c3ce

commit_message:
Allow concurrent tasks to complete after error

Add an option to allow concurrent tasks in a DependencyTaskGroup some time
to run to completion before being cancelled in the event of an error in
another task.

Change-Id: Ie3d63a0d5e8c9fa5f0fa74285b06f732685afcbc

commit_message:
Use /usr/bin/env python instead of /usr/bin/python

The usage of /usr/bin/env ensures that the first interpreter
found in the environment's $PATH variable is used. This should
be preferred.

Change-Id: I9af1b07ccc4364615edb0759249f2cc99037350d

commit_message:
Updates available resources after live migration

A new VM can't be deployed using resources of the VM that has been migrated
to a new host before the periodic task is called after a live migration.

This change calls update_available_resource() after live
migration is completed even before the next periodic task takes place.

Change-Id: I4c879dcfb1e76cfdc95612b6d8010c1081ac45b9
Closes-Bug: #1267862

[{'created': '2014-07-10 15:49:18.000000000', 'message': 'Store original state when suspending

We were losing the original state when suspending a rescued instance. This

commit_message:
Store original state when suspending

We were losing the original state when suspending a rescued instance. This
patch ensures that a suspended rescued instance is restored to the rescued
state on resume.

Closes-Bug: #1342055
Change-Id: I89be60d65eddcfe561794c210b1057fdb157cf41

token flushing: don't override log file

Modify the crontab which flush old tokens to not override the log file,
and avoid deleting previous logs.

Signed-off-by: Emilien Macchi <emilien.macchi@enovance.com>

commit_message:
PowerDNS: Ensure each greenthread uses it's own Session instance

This uses a thread local store, allowing each greenthread to
have it's own session stored correctly. Without this, each
greenthread may end up using a single global session, which
leads to bad things happening.

See also I1ceb33d2bcb531d444ad05cf6cf74b6edd4e7d39

Conflicts:
        designate/backend/impl_powerdns/__init__.py

Change-Id: I7577e33800d947023b9bc939a76f7f78d20c2fb8
Closes-Bug: 1343561

commit_message:
Ensure each greenthread uses it's own Session instance

This uses a thread local store, allowing each greenthread to
have it's own session stored correctly. Without this, each
greenthread may end up using a single global session, which
leads to bad things happening.

Conflicts:
        designate/storage/impl_sqlalchemy/__init__.py

Change-Id: I1ceb33d2bcb531d444ad05cf6cf74b6edd4e7d39
Closes-Bug: 1343211

I picked this admittedly somewhat more complicated approach because I wanted to make a note in the log that something was wrong that should not happen.

"chmod -v" would be an option, but its behavior differs between Linux (always prints out a line with details) and OS X (prints only the file name iff permissions were changed).

The check is done before every ssh/scp call (we don't care about performance, and if something messes with those files, it might be between two calls), so we can't print a line unless the permissions are wrong and must be corrected.

If you think the log message is unnecessary, I am happy to resubmit the simpler solution you suggested.'}, {'account_id': 11889, 'date': '2014-09-01 09:35:20.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+2

revisions:
[{'created': '2014-09-01 06:42:01.000000000', 'message': "labs: check and fix private ssh key permissions

If a user changes the permissions of the Vagrant insecure ssh key,
ssh authentication doesn't work anymore and they are prompted for
a password. To prevent that, check (and adjust, if necessary) file
permissions before using ssh.

Change-Id: I90589553de30ef606c4083a1b9980c2cc80a3b3b
"}]
commit_message:
labs: check and fix private ssh key permissions

If a user changes the permissions of the Vagrant insecure ssh key,
ssh authentication doesn't work anymore and they are prompted for
a password. To prevent that, check (and adjust, if necessary) file
permissions before using ssh.

Change-Id: I90589553de30ef606c4083a1b9980c2cc80a3b3b

[{'created': '2014-09-01 12:40:53.000000000', 'message': 'labs: leave all node VMs running

After a cluster build, the controller VM is running whereas the other
two are not. This inconsistency can be confusing to users. This patch
makes sure all three VMs are running when the cluster build is done.

Change-Id: I2319b06bd94836e74ebc77330cc16549b7582ac1
'}]
commit_message:
labs: leave all node VMs running

After a cluster build, the controller VM is running whereas the other
two are not. This inconsistency can be confusing to users. This patch
makes sure all three VMs are running when the cluster build is done.

Change-Id: I2319b06bd94836e74ebc77330cc16549b7582ac1

commit_message:
Add clean shutdown parameters to power_off()

Adds the timeout and retry_interval parameters to the power_off
method in the virt driver to keep this consistent with the following
change in Nova:

 https://review.openstack.org/#/c/68942

Change-Id: Iebd8eaf067498845836d259c7cbcd8a2a67f05bb
Partially-Implements: blueprint user-defined-shutdown

commit_message:
Fix symlink creation during rollback (systests)

Currently soft link to the folder with bootstrap files
is created in the home directory because argument with
'destination' is missed. The same issue with links to
supervisor configs and version.yaml, because there is
missed space symbol between arguments.

Change-Id: I92384b595c17f5345d1a6db416b4c3f8d112422a

commit_message:
Remove unused Neutron values

These Neutron parameters are not actually needed or used on a Swift
Storage instance. neutron-openvswitch-agent does not even need to be
present on a Swift node.

Change-Id: I5d61cc1d22a719b186e6d89baaf25f119e0416d7

commit_message:
Ensure `pool` exists before creating a flavor

Make sure the pool a flavor relies on exists before creating the flavor.
Raise 400 otherwise.

DocImpact
Flavors creation can now fail with 400 if the pool doesn't exist.

Change-Id: Ib6cc061a92b9c5bc11a3f970dd92bb8b87eb6584

commit_message:
Raise proper HTTP error when flavor doesn't exist

Instead of failing with error 500, raise a proper error and let the user
know that queue creation has failed because the flavor passed in the
metadata does not exist.

Change-Id: I2c41ba1aa790707d9a05c205a09e4b0306c13c78

commit_message:
Add a config option to block the Oozie server port

Oozie workflows may sometimes contain sensitive information in the form of
arguments or configuration parameters to jobs. This is a proposal to optionally
protect against exposure of sensitive config/arg values by blocking access to
the Oozie server via iptables.

Change-Id: I15f8f71f0c0f0d2294b71ee4c179d660367df6a4

commit_message:
Make cells manager use instance object

This makes the nova cells manager to use the Instance object
instead of using a direct database call.

Related to blueprint virt-objects-juno

Change-Id: I8555907280e0d482194ed49a066803d3ddf79c5d

commit_message:
Return full error message for HTTP errors

Non-HeatException, non-remote errors were getting their messages
truncated at the first newline and leaving incomplete error messages the
in json response.  We can only be certain that remote errors raised
through oslo.messaging will conform to the "message + \n + stack_trace"
formula

Closes-Bug: #1358417
Change-Id: I785c6e41101960ea7ceb00c0733c49c2a8aa909f

commit_message:
Fix port residue when instance deletion

A port be implicit-created on ec2 instance creation
if only specify 'SubnetId', so the port id needs to
be stored in instance resource_data so that the port
can be deleted on instance deletion.

Change-Id: I3b685fca26397f8f47d6a732891f06a5360b6487
Closes-bug: #1358581

commit_message:
Changes V3 server_actions extension into v2.1

This patch changes v3 server_actions API to v2.1, and also share v2.1 and v2
test case.
rename server_actions back to instance_actions.
The differences between v2 and v3 are described on the wiki page
https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/NovaAPIv2tov3 .
Partially implements blueprint v2-on-v3-api

Change-Id: I8f11dc5f199711e1c98badfbe0035883d9c15573

commit_message:
Migrate test_server_advanced_ops to tempest client

This patch migrate the server advanced ops scenario tests
from official client to tempest clients.

This patch also correct some logging
For example -
During Suspending and Resuming the instance current state of instance
was wrong in log meggase.

Partially-implements: bp:tempest-client-scenarios

Change-Id: I5bad550e64d8226e479c28b74378d812a629e2d0

commit_message:
xenapi: adding ipxe_boot_menu_url image property

Allows configuration of the ipxe boot_menu_url from an image property,
falling back to the default configuration.

The image property is:
ipxe_boot_menu_url

Implements blueprint xenapi-set-ipxe-url-as-img-metadata

commit_message:
Upgrades, added documentation for user in case of errors

We have some known issues which we cannot
address right now, in order to make user's
live better, we decided to add documentation
which will help user to workaround problems
which he can have during the upgrade.

Change-Id: I7381545f027d06d04b4144a466830af1e4a59b92
Closes-bug: #1362685

commit_message:
Update share_network obj after db update

With first usage of share-network, backend driver receives share_network
without 'cidr' value for subnet, because obj was gotten before db update
with 'cidr' value. So we add additional re-get in case network-allocations
stuff used.

Change-Id: Id3ae1cbde96c583423943ad72f4879b1a71e942a
Closes-Bug: #1358707

Great! 
We just have to remember to come back and complete the axfr response message with the SOA record as first and last RR.

Also, as far as RRset upper limit, dnspython should not have an [artificial] limit. Since we are using TCP (as opposed to UDP) we have a lot of room. But we can always send multiple messages to accomplish the AXFR so long as the first message starts with SOA, followed by one or more messages containing RRsets and then finally the SOA again.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-08-18 22:33:44.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Verified-1

commit_message:
Expose SOA and NS records

Designate currently generates and hides
each zones NS and SOA records, this
can be confusing for users who expect all
records to be visible in the API.

Change-Id: Ib23f3eb0ae196553c92a28b054ec3cc63333ecef

commit_message:
Fixes to build from trunc feature

1. Fix public Gerrit URL in config
2. Fix adding package dependencies to local mirror
3. Fix for including built packages into ISO.

Change-Id: I324fc5bcb32c12a394091115f5800e2f7c278f27
Blueprint: openstack-from-master

commit_message:
Refactor DB model access functions - DO NOT MERGE

The _get_collection and _get_collection_query functions are a bit
messy, naming conventions and extensibility wise. This patch refactors
these function in the purpose of reducing code-duplications and
improving extensibility.

Change-Id: If0738099f1b02908e198b326d641719ad9e71055
Closes-bug: #1350852

commit_message:
Prevent problem with nodes reboot using Cobbler

Sometimes Cobbler return success status for reboot
operation which really failed. We try additionally
reboot this nodes using ssh.

Change-Id: Idba1e1734f8446381acedef42a93e88fe4248d63
Closes-Bug: #1318567

commit_message:
Rebase hardware pollsters to use new inspector interface

Change all the hardware pollsters to use new inspector interface
inspect_generic(), and remove the old interfaces.

Partial implements: blueprint snmp-improvement.
Partial-Bug: 1286132

Change-Id: Icc566ec8c4dbe1c0883c7e0d653480c5659f30b9

Thank you for your first contribution to OpenStack.

    Your patch will now be tested automatically by OpenStack testing frameworks
    and once the automatic tests pass, it will be reviewed by other friendly
    developers. They will give you feedback and may require you to refine it.

    People seldom get their patch approved on the first try, so don't be
    concerned if requested to make corrections. Feel free to modify your patch
    and resubmit a new change-set.

    Patches usually take 3 to 7 days to be reviewed so be patient and be
    available on IRC to ask and answer questions about your work. The more you
    participate in the community the more rewarding it is for you. You may also
    notice that the more you get to know people and get to be known, the faster
    your patches will be reviewed and eventually approved. Get to know others
    and become known by doing code reviews: anybody can do it, and it's a
    great way to learn the code base.

    Thanks again for supporting OpenStack, we look forward to working with you.

cmd: add nova-serialproxy service

Adds a websocket proxy that is compatible with Nova
serial ports.

Co-Authored-By: Vladan Popovic <vpopovic@redhat.com>
Co-Authored-By: Ian Wells <iawells@cisco.com>
Co-Authored-By: Sushma Korati <sushma_korati@persistent.co.in>

Partial-Implements: blueprint serial-ports

commit_message:
console: add serial console module

Adds new module console/serial.py to handle configuration
and TCP ports management for the feature serial-ports.

Co-Authored-By: Vladan Popovic <vpopovic@redhat.com>
Co-Authored-By: Ian Wells <iawells@cisco.com>
Co-Authored-By: Sushma Korati <sushma_korati@persistent.co.in>

DocImpact: new group of option 'serial_console'
Partial-Implements: blueprint serial-ports
Change-Id: Icb7f3569a29a5fab9aaa3a2d441f5fe4e5b55b9f

commit_message:
Rewrite images tests with mock

test_images module was using fixtures to test ironic.common.images
module. Mock is now used instead. New tests added. fetch_to_raw is
not tested as it is going to be removed as mentioned here:
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/115974/

Change-Id: Id931b6d9cc1213f1347a9324510580e14c601412
Closes-bug: #1361672

commit_message:
Reapply post_start_hooks after container deploy

Workaround to avoid conditions where some iptables
rules are not being created during deployment due
to heavy system load. The workaround simply
re-applies the same post start hooks to all
containers, improving the chances of rules
being applied.

Change-Id: I153146bb5b182cb18f49ae8bd92e8ee37d7334de
Closes-Bug: #1362159

Thank you for your first contribution to OpenStack.

    Your patch will now be tested automatically by OpenStack testing frameworks
    and once the automatic tests pass, it will be reviewed by other friendly

    People seldom get their patch approved on the first try, so don't be
    concerned if requested to make corrections. Feel free to modify your patch
    and resubmit a new change-set.

    Patches usually take 3 to 7 days to be reviewed so be patient and be
    available on IRC to ask and answer questions about your work. The more you
    participate in the community the more rewarding it is for you. You may also
    notice that the more you get to know people and get to be known, the faster
    your patches will be reviewed and eventually approved. Get to know others
    and become known by doing code reviews: anybody can do it, and it's a
    great way to learn the code base.

commit_message:
Convert v3 cells API to v2.1

This patch changes v3 cells API to v2.1 and makes v2
unit tests share between v2 and v2.1.

This patch also delete the V3 cells API tests.

The differences between v2 and v3 are described on the wiki page
https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/NovaAPIv2tov3.

Partially implements blueprint v2-on-v3-api

Change-Id: Iacfd1881ff24eb3bfc73006244044fc139897eda

commit_message:
Convert v3 server metadata plugin to v2.1

This patch converts v3 server metadata plugin to v2.1 and makes v2
unit tests share between v2 and v2.1.

The differences between v2 and v3 are described on the wiki page
https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/NovaAPIv2tov3.

Partially implements blueprint v2-on-v3-api

Change-Id: I619a7323f515234d15000af356277dbf3d91231f

stable/5.0 Changes for support vcenter

commit_message:
Cleanup apt cache after grub install

Grub installation happens in finalize.d so cleanup should be done after this.

This reapplies I6322b8b529e31fd1b7251dd9e07cc85f442f7e81 after the revert,
but working.

Change-Id: Ie1873e64d407552da37a8dbedc13c3adbf79c085

commit_message:
Fix downgrade in first DB migration script after havana

The first DB upgrade script after havana, e197124d4b9, adds a unique
constraint on a table. The downgrade must drop the unique constraint,
but it cannot do so while a foreign key constraint is in effect for any
of the columns that are part of the unique constraint. It turns out
there is a FK constraint on the pool_id column.

This change fixes the downgrade by temporarily dropping the pool_id FK
constraint before dropping the unique constraint, then restoring the
pool_id FK constraint.

Closes-bug: #1363332

Change-Id: Ic7e8d5a0b7781d396cd55d6ebc7aa9468251bce8

commit_message:
Improve install guide security content

I improved security content in the installation guide as
follows:

1) Renamed basic environment 'passwords' section to 'security' to
   generalize topic.
2) Generalized existing content.
3) Added content about administrative privilege requirements
   including potential interference with deployment automation
   tools.

Recommend backporting to Icehouse.

Change-Id: Ide9785728c7b52ee1dc59a533b3486b99ee11139
Closes-Bug: #1311426
backport: icehouse

commit_message:
Add baremetal API tests

This patch set adds tests og below Ironic APIs:

* GET /v1/nodes/(node_uuid)/management/boot_device
* PUT /v1/nodes/(node_uuid)/management/boot_device
* GET /v1/nodes/(node_uuid)/management/boot_device/supported

Partially Implements blueprint: missing-baremetal-api-test

Change-Id: Ia54a8b1272e4990d08deed90f8d962670f49be8d

commit_message:
Not compressing a specific js bloc

There is a js inline block in _conf.html which seems to generate wrong
key in the offline manifest.

Since it's a small portion, there is no performance issue innot compressing it
and Offline compression works again

Change-Id: I6dd9095cb8ad6f024b886a6ba3b419c52cb41425
Closes-Bug: 1155765

commit_message:
test_neutron_resources to read template's values

test_neutron_resources create resources based on defined template
but the expected values are hard coded in this tests those should be
read from template.

Change-Id: I5ecc8742bab4c5d940c134945816c47acfba2282

commit_message:
Adds Ironic set/get boot device API test

Adds Ironic API tests to validate the management interface for set/get
boot device and get the supported boot devices.

Implements: blueprint new-management-interface
Change-Id: I23ad1479858f5b116c1e35242d7eee10c9626d32

revisions:
[{'created': '2014-08-25 04:28:21.000000000', 'message': 'Add a test for inline parameter of TempURL

From Swift Icehouse version, TempURL supports "inline" query parameter to
prevent from downloading a target object with browser by causing
"Content-Disposition: inline" to be set on the response.

Partially implements blueprint add-icehouse-swift-tests

Change-Id: I453e58c07078ba130e0360750f24bd75ca1396d5
'}]
commit_message:
Add a test for inline parameter of TempURL

From Swift Icehouse version, TempURL supports "inline" query parameter to
prevent from downloading a target object with browser by causing
"Content-Disposition: inline" to be set on the response.

Partially implements blueprint add-icehouse-swift-tests

Change-Id: I453e58c07078ba130e0360750f24bd75ca1396d5

commit_message:
Add a nicer trace prompt for $PS4

Since we are standardizing on bash for shell scripts, we may as well
tell it to use a trace prompt that is vastly more useful for debugging.

This patchset changes $PS4 to prepend the script name and line number to
every line output in a debug trace.

Change-Id: I4ec5c0253295724a9580f86fd30082acd89d155d

[{'created': '2014-08-28 18:40:49.000000000', 'message': 'Update neutron network node section to adjust MTU

I updated the neutron network node section to discuss the
implications of tunneling protocols such as GRE, provide
potential solutions, and recommend using DHCP to adjust the
instance MTU.

This patch does not address the equivalent section for the
deprecated OVS plug-in.

Also, this patch does not backport the glossary updates.

commit_message:
Update neutron network node section to adjust MTU

I updated the neutron network node section to discuss the
implications of tunneling protocols such as GRE, provide
potential solutions, and recommend using DHCP to adjust the
instance MTU.

This patch does not address the equivalent section for the
deprecated OVS plug-in.

Change-Id: Ia8dd9fe78d5c845c85bfde0d96481a55f754e121
Closes-Bug: #1361310
(cherry picked from commit 951c047c28fe5b2670e5d3364d00ce30d120ab62)

commit_message:
Provide a quick way to run flake8

"run_tests.sh -p" always checks every file for errors even though you
have probably only changed a handful. This patch adds "run_tests.sh -8"
which only checks the files that were modified in the HEAD commit or
in the current working tree.

It is borrowed from the recent nova commit b011325cc6.
The related ML post is:
http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2014-August/043346.html

Change-Id: Ieeabf1b79a0790af8bde3144dca59b4245a0b79a

commit_message:
Changes V3 remote_console extension into v2.1

This patch changes v3 remote_console API to v2.1 and makes v2
unit tests share between v2 and v2.1.
The differences between v2 and v3 are described on the wiki page
https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/NovaAPIv2tov3.

Partially implements blueprint v2-on-v3-api

Change-Id: I5f15ec39d7201b2da3d7afbf1d0774e64e68c8fe

subject: Use common get_instance function in v2 consoles extension

commit_message:
Use common get_instance function in v2 consoles extension

This patch use common get_instance function in v2 consoles extension.
That can make the instance behavior consistent with v2.1 api. Then
v2.1 and v2 can share same unittest.

Change-Id: Idf501be21178c3c97b1693e48d3fd13b97525299

commit_message:
Sync latest strutils from oslo-incubator

We have had a request from Tristan Cacqueray to pull in the latest
strutils.  The request is driven by a need to get improvements in
place that make strutils.mask_password more secure.

-------------------------------------

Head of oslo-incubator:
commit 80a08a413fb0f23a056eca2d273b167f0a09bab6
Merge: 83c4098 d73f3b1
Author: Jenkins <jenkins@review.openstack.org>
Date:   Mon Aug 25 14:32:36 2014 +0000

    Merge "Remove unused/mutable default args"

--------------------------------------

This sync pulls in the following change:

66142c34 - Make strutils.mask_password more secure

--------------------------------------

Change-Id: Ie51d316a30bed40996db6cd860dbb9cb173e5ac6
Partial-bug: 1345233

I can't seem to find the comments in the patch though.'}, {'account_id': 1941, 'date': '2014-08-29 06:32:28.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 16:

or we could just wait for Gloria's response too :)"}, {'account_id': 841, 'date': '2014-08-29 07:14:44.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 16:

I understand cinder always use qemu-img to do this and it is not configurable. It is okay. What I am concerning is just whether we should have a setting option in Horizon side so that operators wants to disable this feature or not.

Note that I am okay that we merge it first and then we discuss the necessity of the setting.'}, {'account_id': 11880, 'date': '2014-08-29 16:47:54.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 16:

Hi Lin and Motoki-san, 

It is odd, I added the comments regarding qemu-img at patch set 6, it is not on the file, it is on the top of the commit message...it is odd, Lin's comments are all gone too. Anyway, cinder always use qemu-img, it is not configurable based on Walter Boring the cinder core."}, {'account_id': 11880, 'date': '2014-08-29 16:55:57.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 16:

Hi Motoki-san, 

Just afraid of loosing my comments again :) since it has the same situation as my comments on patch set 6...so respond here regarding the following message:

"	
Akihiro Motoki		Aug 28 10:57 PM
Hmm.... but if horizon displays the action menu, users tend to think "Oh the useful feature is added" but it sometimes doesn't work. It potentially brings some confusion to users and operators may want to disable this feature to avoid confusion to their users. This is the reason I commented it in the above comment. It might be discussed later.
Thought?
"

The action provides the convenience for the users to run the command in UI. The action is consistent with the cinder command.'}, {'account_id': 841, 'date': '2014-08-29 18:10:06.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 16:

I think we are thinking things from different point of view.
I agree that adding an action provides a convenient way. There is no objection at this point.

On the other hand, as you commented copy-volume-to-image feature depends on a backend used (succeed with 3par, failed with lefthand array). Even though Cinder and cinder CLI exposes the feature even if some backends does not support it. In this context, end-users need to consider whether they can use this feature because “ah. I am using this backend, so I can/cannot use it.”.

Horizon has a bit different view on it. We try to avoid confusion as possible as we can.
Even if the backend project does not provide a way to know some feature (or more detail) is available or not, Horizon provides a way to toggle on/off the feature through Horizon settings. It is not related to whether Cinder has no configuration on this.

If some operator use lefthand array, I think he/she want not to display this action. What can he/she do?

It seems you don’t want to add Horizon option. I don’t want to spend more time on this specific topic, so I don’t object to go as-is and if we receive a bug report on this we can add an option to toggle on/off the feature if someone work on it (though I don’t agree it).

I would like to leave the final approval to other reviewers due to the above my thought.

Finally, do you address Lin's comment on the message in this patch or in a followup patch before giving +2 from me?"}, {'account_id': 11880, 'date': '2014-08-29 19:00:06.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 16:

Hi Motoki-san, 

Thanks for the comments and spending time thinking about it. Really appreciate it! I 100% agree with you that we should avoid confusion for the users.  

Just want to get the clarification,  when volume is available (normal case), it works OK for 3par and lefthand. Only if volume is in-use, then it gets into a situation where the backend matters. Common case is to upload volume to image when volume is NOT in-use. My 2 cents, adding a setting for this kind of situation will not make things easier for the users...

Regarding Lin's comments, Lin okied that I could open a defect once this bp is merged. I plan to do that. If you want me to address his comments before you approve it, I can do that. However I will join the pain of zuul queue and be at the mercy of Jenkins :(. Let me know. 

Again thank you so much for your comments!"}, {'account_id': 11880, 'date': '2014-08-29 20:24:12.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 16:

Hi Motoki-san and Lin, 

One more thought...

When volume is in-use, it means, the volume is attached to a instance. when volume is available, it means, no instance attached. 

Maybe to make things easier for user...will not allow the action show up when volume is in-use? However this will not be consistent with the current cinder command.'}, {'account_id': 11973, 'date': '2014-08-29 21:08:32.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 16: Code-Review+1

Reviewed feature on In-Use. Looks good.'}, {'account_id': 11880, 'date': '2014-08-31 06:34:37.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 16:

Hi Motoki-san, 

Regarding upload-volume(in-use)-to image case, we could leave it as it is for now. Later if it becomes an issue for the users we can enter a defect to add a setting to flip on/off the action.'}, {'account_id': 841, 'date': '2014-08-31 16:58:19.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 16: Code-Review+2 Workflow+1

commit_message:
Upload volume to image service

Expose the functionality of the 'cinder upload-to-image' command
in the UI. It allows user to upload of a volume whose status is
in-use or available to the Glance image service.

When the volume is in-use, user still wants to uploads that volume
to image, user needs to set force to be True. The force checkbox
only shows when the volume is in-use. Whether it can
succesfully upload the volume to image depends on if the storage
array that volume is created in supports attaching multiple instances
to the volume. Not all arrays supports that. There is no api that
can detect if array supports that before cinder actutally uploads
the volume in-use to image.

The container format is 'bare'. The list of disk formats are
based on the format supportability by both glance and qemu-img.
cinder uses qemu-img for converting the volume to a image.

Implements: blueprint cinder-volume-upload-image

Change-Id: Ie5fc26c260e5f4ef2700c40c8cea6150fdbd522c

commit_message:
backend for policy endpoint extension

This patch implements the sql backend and manager level for the
policy endpoint extension.  The controller level will be added in
a follow on patch.

Partially implememts: bp endpoint-policy

commit_message:
Fail workflow if any task fails

Workbook gets stuck in RUNNING state if one of its child tasks
fails.  This change puts it in ERROR state instead.

Change-Id: Idadea9886983fc792f4b164da7c07062c29c66da
Closes-Bug: #1346356

commit_message:
Transform Exception args to strings when exceptions

Import the following change from Cinder to fix a problem with translated
exceptions.

Co-Authored-By: git-harry <git-harry@live.co.uk>

Author: git-harry <git-harry@live.co.uk>
Date:   Thu Apr 17 10:49:49 2014 +0100

    CinderException args to strings when exceptions

    CinderException message and kwargs are converted to strings if the
    argument is itself an exception.

    Exceptions passed as arguments to CinderException happen in many
    areas
    of the code. This causes an error when oslo.messaging tries to
    serialise
    the exception.

    Change-Id: I1399c939bbca47ab8362ac3bbe0e9a349c6d5572
    Closes-Bug: #1301249

Change-Id: If36f1af0b2e9cc7ec263bdacfe5aa4d49c4c9b85

commit_message:
Scheduler: Allow a grace period when cancelling tasks

Previously, we always cancelled a task immediately. This allows us to
optionally allow it to run for up to a specified maximum grace period
before being cancelled (this assumes that the task continues to be
driven by calls to step()).

Change-Id: Id7fcc9ecf5c1704d523826f1ba37411ffd479793

commit_message:
Fix LOG format issue in nova.virt.disk.vfs.guestfs

Wrong string format result in that exception can't
be record into log in nova.virt.disk.vfs.guestfs.

Change-Id: I5ea44c2132e704e8466c626198063f43a3355686
Closes-Bug: #1362073

commit_message:
Handle non dict metadata in server metadata V2 API

While creating or updating the server metadata, requested metadata
should be in form of dictionary.
Currently if it is not in that form then, 500 error is being return
which should be 400.

This patch adds such request check for V2 API and adds its UT

Change-Id: Ifcd4f9d352de7b2676beff319b641547b8952566

commit_message:
Remove python-guestfs package

Starting with Icehouse, the nova compute service no longer appears
to rely on the python-guestfs package. Package already removed from
Juno version.

Change-Id: I99a2edbfb3a7fb78e22a3e4d7726c2e4d2848a5d
Closes-Bug: #1360598

commit_message:
Add sort_key and sort_dir for server list api

Since the compute api now supporting sort_dir and sort_key [1], we may
need to add this to the REST api.

[1]: https://github.com/openstack/nova/blob/master/nova/compute/api.py#L1790

DocImpact

Change-Id: Ie59d4844be77c426dacf765ce2feef97d227ac2d
Closes-bug: #1361554

commit_message:
Explicitly handle exception ConsoleTypeUnavailable for v2 consoles

In v3 remote_console extension, the exception ConsoleTypeUnavailable
is catched by explicitly. This patch changes the v2 api as same way,
and backport v3 unittest into v2 api.

Change-Id: I14f74e4a4b4ee84713b48cfc00d3f132726f9316

commit_message:
Corrected GlusterFS driver info on snapshots

The current docs state that the GlusterFS driver does not support
snapshots and clone. This is no longer true.

This patch updates the documentation accordingly.

Change-Id: I0a6f5ba84e846c117a7f425e41b4bf28dfe552e6
Partial-Bug: #1279185

commit_message:
Fix test mistake with requests-mock

body= parameters are supposed to be io objects. This is obviously during
the conversion from HTTPretty.

Change-Id: Ia8ec9294e054e2231aa4a5e2633e2b7d5d15066a
Closes-Bug: #1363632

Apic drivers enhancements (second approach): L2 refactor

- refactor to leverage Client's transactional capabilities
- General refactor to improve the driver's reliability

commit_message:
Detect neutron endpoint on-the-fly

This change does the following:
- reverts commit 04de60093b602c2eac4a612df5d4a2e31424a25d
- reimplements Resource.is_using_neutron to check for neutron by
  attempting to create a neutron client
- fix mocking in tests for changes which landed after 04de600

If there is no 'network' entry in the service catalog then
keystoneclient will raise an EndpointNotFound. The context will
already have a keystone client cached which has a full service catalog
locally, so calling is_using_neutron should have no particular overhead.

This fixes a tripleo regression where the autodetection is triggered
before keystone is ready, so that heat-engine fails to start. This
race does not affect devstack as keystone is fully configured before
heat services are started.

Not adding config option networking_service will also prevent
extra work required by downstream installation tools.

Change-Id: I45a6154fa560f672d8d1942bf57f39601110bfc6
Closes-Bug: #1362812

commit_message:
Renames snapshot 'pre-installed' on controller node

Renames snapshot 'pre-installed' to 'openstack-controller_installed'
which is more accurate description for the snapshot.

This snapshot can be used to revert back to stable functioning
controller node, which ready and does not require any further
installation or configuration.

Change-Id: I1c9ce714955dec66c9979ac8a86c38d703017f9c

commit_message:
Adds cinder snapshot to the controller node

Snapshot 'cinder_installed' will contain the following packages

    1. cinder-api
    2. cinder-scheduler
    3. lvm2
    4. cinder-volume

This shapshot installs and configures cinder controller and cinder
volume services. Also configures keystone to authenticate with cinder.

This snapshot can be used to obtain stable running version of
controller node and can be used to revert back to this point in case
the students break the cluster.

Change-Id: I0ca7a0b48c455f6ce6c68df5d99bf3edb8a92f84

commit_message:
Adds horizon snapshot to the controller node

Snapshot 'horizon_installed' will contain the following packages

    1. openstack-dashboard
    2. memcached

This shapshot installs horizon.

This snapshot can be used to obtain stable running version of
controller node and can be used to revert back to this point in case
the students break the cluster.

Change-Id: Ie1c2d1047942db390519f11d233156fea1959a09

commit_message:
labs: replace VM_BASE_NAME with local variable

There is no need for users to customize the name of the temporary VM
used for building the base disk. This patch removes that option.

Change-Id: I1e3eebf0c9f1098623d8f4ab50d938211cc78b6f

commit_message:
Add the arch/big picture omnigraffle diagram

To avoid losing this diagram again let's keep
it in the source tree so that others can modify
it and extend it as they desire (and also prevents
it from disappearing).

Will need omnigraffle to view:

https://www.omnigroup.com/omnigraffle

Change-Id: I44eb15722c9d6f2c63d965ff8f849efbdf15bbfb

commit_message:
Adds nova snapshot to the controller node

Snapshot 'nova-controller_installed' will contain the following
packages

    1. nova-api
    2. nova-cert
    3. nova-conductor
    4. nova-consoleauth
    5. nova-novncproxy
    6. nova-scheduler
    7. python-novaclient

Installs and configures nova, configures keystone to authenticate with
nova.

This snapshot can be used to obtain stable running version of
controller node and can be used to revert back to this point in case
the students break the cluster.

Change-Id: I4c4d2ff51cd46e19ea9679f7f536d23ca0317bb0

commit_message:
Adds glance snapshot to the controller node

Snapshot 'glance_installed' will contain the following packages

    1. glance

Glance will be installed and configured, also configures keystone
to authenticate glance. Adds Cirros_x86_64 to glance.

This snapshot can be used to obtain stable running version of
controller node and can be used to revert back to this point in case
the students break the cluster.

Change-Id: If97fdb04cfd1495e85a4c2cc44328c555caff0f6

commit_message:
Instance Action Dashboard Blueprint

Create a new dashboard in Horizon to show the actions taken on the
tenant's instances in reverse date order (latest first). This provides
the user with a view of what's been happening in their environment, and
any errors that have occurred.

Co-Authored-By: Nicolas Simonds <nicolas.simonds@metacloud.com>
Co-Authored-By: David Lapsley <david.lapsley@metacloud.com>
Co-Authored-By: Diana Whitten <diana.whitten@metacloud.com>
Implements: blueprint instance-actions-dashboard
Change-Id: I9cf54db7c2c65ac4679587fa2d8d185a04ae25dc

commit_message:
Renames 'pre-installed' on network node

Renames snapshot 'pre-installed' to 'openstack-network_installed'
which is more accurate description for the snapshot.

This snapshot can be used to revert back to stable functioning
controller node, which ready and does not require any further
installation or configuration.

Change-Id: I438b03c29ec4ba285a43abb184d59f40bd73d8f4

commit_message:
metering driver default value is different in code and config file

We defined the metering driver is IptablesMeteringDriver in config,
but in code, the driver is NoopMeteringDriver.

Change-Id: Ia4fb6751e8a9919f844ef27a303e2fa95b46670e
Closes-Bug: #1360958

commit_message:
Datacenter moid should not be tuple

Remove the comma, because it will convert the string to tuple
Closes-bug: #1362480

Change-Id: I2debb76bae26fe3d437a431f2946f66a1cbe6851

commit_message:
VMware: Disable suds caching

The default cache implementation in suds store pickled objects in a
predictable path in /tmp which could lead to attacks. This patch
turns off suds caching to address this security issue.

Change-Id: I7daaa25a0677004e03896298e9c3026d5c33c6ac
Closes-Bug: #1341954

to image. This results in volume being stuck in uploading state for

commit_message:
VMware: Handle exceptions raised by image update

Exceptions raised by glance image update are not handled while writing
to image. This results in volume being stuck in uploading state for
a long time even after image transfer failure. This patch fixes the
exception handling.

Change-Id: I7651c96968caa49c5421d68ee4dbe9e55f7f53b1
Closes-Bug: #1357239
Partial-Bug: #1269345

commit_message:
Adds keystone snapshot to the controller node

Snapshot 'keystone_installed' will contain the following packages

    1. keystone

This snapshot will also configure keystone as required for OpenStack.
This snapshot can be used to obtain stable running version of
controller node and can be used to revert back to this point in case
the students break the cluster.

Change-Id: I473f3970e46666bbf55d092905ed1ca740c4196d

commit_message:
Change v3 flavor_rxtx to v2.1

This patch changes v3 flavor_rxtx API to v2.1 and makes v2
unit tests share between v2 and v2.1.

The differences between v2 and v3 are described on the wiki page
https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/NovaAPIv2tov3.

Partially implements blueprint v2-on-v3-api

Change-Id: I0b79be078ff2b2ca682f1f061f40c81d4487c7de

commit_message:
Merge BadRequest tests of v2 quota_sets API

In test_quotas, there are BadRequest tests of v2 quota_sets API.
Most parts of them are duplicated.
This patch merges them for the readability and clarifying their purposes.

Change-Id: I4313b2a80819260e9363f457ba271689308b145f

commit_message:
Adds pre-openstack snapshot to the controller node

Snapshot 'pre-openstack_installed' will contain the following packages

    1. RabbitMQ
    2. MySQL

This snapshot can be used to obtain stable running version of
controller node and can be used to revert back to this point in case
the students break the cluster.

Change-Id: Ie2ada08409a9a639439751a4329fab2ca7b803f8
